[2] Saint-Barthelemy
Date: Wed 12 Mar 2008
Source: Point Epidemiologique, Ministere de la Sante, de la Jeunesse
et des Sports, Institut Ville Sanitaire No. 9 [in French, trans. &
summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.invs.sante.fr/presse/2008/le_point_sur/dengue_pep_st_barth_130308/PEP_SBSM_2008_9_dengue.pdf>



The weekly number of cases of clinically suspected dengue is still
above the epidemic threshold (about 20 cases per week). The number of
laboratory confirmed cases is constant (around 8 cases). A new
laboratory confirmed case was hospitalized during the 10th
epidemiological week [week of 9 Mar 2008].

Since the beginning of the pre-alert in mid-November [2007], it is
estimated that more than 400 people have gone to a general
practitioner physician for a syndrome compatible with dengue. During
the same period, 6 adults with severe forms [of dengue] have been
hospitalized.

Since December 2007, the [dengue virus] serotype most often
identified has been DEN-1. Nevertheless, the [virus] serotype DEN-2
also circulates.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[A map showing the location of the French overseas collectivity of
