[3] Saint Martin
Date: Wed 12 Mar 2008
Source: Point Epidemiologique, Ministere de la Sante, de la Jeunesse
et des Sports
Ville Sanitaire No. 9 [in French, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.invs.sante.fr/presse/2008/le_point_sur/dengue_pep_st_barth_130308/PEP_SBSM_2008_9_dengue.pdf>


The number of clinically suspected [dengue] cases observed in the
past few weeks has not continued to decline and remains higher than
the epidemic threshold (35 cases estimated). However, no laboratory
confirmed cases have been identified. Nor have there been any
laboratory confirmed hospitalizations since January [2008].

Since the beginning of the epidemic (2nd week of November [2007]),
there have been 1900 estimated total clinically suspected [dengue]
cases. Over the same period, the number of hospitalizations for
laboratory confirmed dengue was 17, including 12 adults (of which 8
were serious forms [of dengue]) and 5 children (with only common
[dengue] forms).

Monitoring has detected dengue [virus] serotype DEN-1 since
mid-November [2007].

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[It is strange that none of the 35 suspected dengue cases clinically
diagnosed in 2008 have been laboratory confirmed. Perhaps they have a
flu outbreak now instead. - Mod.JW]

