[6] Brazil (Amazonas)
Date: Fri 14 Mar 2008
Source: Portal Amazonia, Diario de Amazonas-TM report [in Portuguese,
trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://portalamazonia.globo.com:80/noticias.php?idN=65170&idLingua=1>


Thus far in 2008, 2 children have died of DHF and these cases are
under investigation. This is the same [number of deaths] registered
during all of 2007.

According to Evandro Melo, the director-president of the Foundation
for Health Surveillance (SVM), the deaths occurred in children aged 7
years. The cases were recorded in the 1st 2 months of the year.
According to SVM records, the children who died lived in [the capital]
Manaus and there have been no suspected cases in the interior of the
state.

The data on the disease recorded by the state Secretary of Health
will be released today [14 Mar 2008] in the summary of operation
"Impact" combating dengue. The operation started 2 weeks ago and is
being carried out in partnership with the fire department and the
armed forces.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
<promed@promedmail.org>

