[7] New Caledonia
Date: 20 Mar 2008
Source: Radio New Zealand International [edited]
<http://www.rnzi.com/pages/news.php?op=read&id=38699>


The number of registered dengue cases in New Caledonia this year has
passed 200.

Despite efforts to contain the spread of the mosquito-borne disease,
the number of cases has grown 3-fold in less than 3 weeks.

Most of the cases have been found in the Noumea area.

In late February [2008] the pre-epidemic status was upgraded and
awareness campaigns were stepped up.

In 2003, as many as 20 people in New Caledonia died of dengue fever.

--
