[8] Philippines (Zamboanga City)
Date: Wed 12 Mar 2008
Source: Inquirer.net - Philippines [edited]
<http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/breakingnews/regions/view/20080312-124284/UPDATE-Dengue-outbreak-declared-in-Zamboanga>


The city government has declared a dengue outbreak following a sharp
increase in the number of people afflicted by the mosquito-borne
disease during the last 3 months.

Based on records from the city health office, 406 dengue cases had
been monitored from January up to 11 Mar [2008]; 2 deaths had been
recorded. Mayor Celso Lobregat said before a local health summit here
on Tuesday [11 Mar 2008] that the declaration was made on
recommendation of city health officer Dr Rodelin Agbulos.

"We are declaring a dengue fever outbreak in Zamboanga City and we
have directed the City Health Office (CHO) to source out a contingency
budget for fumigation, which is about PHP 300 000 [USD 7224],"
Lobregat said.

He called on village officials and residents to cooperate to fight the
menace. "Barangay [neighborhood] officials and the committee on health
have to be very active because this campaign cannot be done by the
City Health office alone or even efforts from City Hall or city
government officials, we need all the support from everyone," Lobregat
said.

He said among the immediate measures taken was a citywide cleanup
drive. Dengue-carrying mosquitoes lay their [eggs that hatch into]
larvae in [both] clean [and] stagnant waters.

Agbulos said the target of the cleanup drive are villages, where the
incidence of dengue was exceptionally high. Agbulos confirmed the
sharp increase in the number of dengue cases reported to the CHO
during the past weeks. He said in 2007, there were only 90 cases
monitored from January to 5 Mar, compared to the
same period this year [2008], which has 386 cases already. "It's
alarming (but) we are trying to do everything to control (the spread
of the disease)," he said.

The declaration of an outbreak was the 2nd for the city since 2005,
when dengue cases shot up to 610 over a 6-month period.

[Byline: Julie Alipala]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED Rapporteur A-Lan Banks


[ProMED-mail Rapporteur Brent Barrett forwarded a report from the Sun
Star
<http://www.sunstar.com.ph/static/net/2008/03/17/city.health.dengue.cases.on.the.rise.in.zambo.(6.28.p.m.).html>
indicating that the number of dengue cases in Zamboanga City have
soared further, bringing the total to 434; 28 cases had been added to
the registered cases after the declaration of a dengue alert in the
city. The anti-dengue campaign is operating in 13 villages tagged as
"hot spots". Zamboanga City is located on the far SW part of Mindanao
Island. A map of the area can be accessed at
<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zamboanga_City>. - Mod.TY]

