[9] Philippines (Central Visayas)
Date: Thu 6 Mar 2008
Source: GMA News TV [edited]
<http://www.gmanews.tv/story/83583/Dengue-kills-25-in-Central-Visayas---report>


Department of Health (DOH) [Region] 7 recorded a total of 1045 dengue
cases admitted to different hospitals from 1 Jan to 1 Mar [2008].
Within these 2 months, at least 25 died of dengue fever in Central
Visayas.

The Regional Epidemiology and Surveillance Unit (Resu) estimated the
case [fatality] rate to be about 76 percent higher than in the same
period last year [2007], when there were only 594 cases with 7 deaths
in the region.

Most of the patients were 6-10 years old, although a 5-month-old baby
was recorded as the youngest and a 74-year-old adult as the oldest
cases. Resu also recorded an equal number of male and female patients.

Cebu City still ranks 1st in the top 10 list of municipalities and
cities with a high number of dengue cases in Region 7, with its 251
cases and 10 deaths. In the same period last year [2007] , there were
only 168 cases and 2 deaths in the city.

However, according to the City Epidemiology Statistics and
Surveillance Unit, the City already documented 408 cases with 12
deaths as of 1 Mar [2008]. This is about 172 percent higher compared
to the figures from the same period last year [2007].

Last year [2007], the dengue virus hit 2107 Cebu City residents, 51
of whom died. This number was 120 percent higher than in 2006, when
only 957 cases and 27 deaths were recorded.

City Hall already recorded 234 cases in January [2008] and 174 last
month [February 2008]. In 2007, it only recorded 69 cases for January
and 81 for February.

City Hall's Anti-Dengue Task Force plans to mobilize the massive
spraying of anti-dengue chemicals in Barangay Inayawan this week in
close coordination with
the City Health Department.

Meanwhile, dengue cases in other cities in Central Visayas also
doubled. Residents are urged to help prevent it by ridding their
homes and surroundings of open receptacles where water may gather and
mosquitoes breed.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED Rapporteur A-Lan Banks

[A map of Philippine provinces, showing Cebu, can be accessed at
<http://www.reliefweb.int/mapc/asi_se/cnt/phil/phl_ad.html>,
and an interactive map of Cebu Province showing Cebu city and other
cities can be accessed at
<http://encarta.msn.com/map_701511592/Cebu_city_Philippines.html>. - Mod.TY]

